{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":193892,"duration_api_ms":295592,"num_turns":13,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"cb7f0d2a-7752-426f-9439-91a1275fadea","total_cost_usd":1.1754233,"usage":{"input_tokens":2176,"cache_creation_input_tokens":72288,"cache_read_input_tokens":484622,"output_tokens":3482,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":72288,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":210,"outputTokens":14012,"cacheReadInputTokens":1987673,"cacheCreationInputTokens":91476,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.38338229999999995,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000},"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":2176,"outputTokens":3482,"cacheReadInputTokens":484622,"cacheCreationInputTokens":72288,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.792041,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"evidence":["All 102 milestone_record tests pass (0 failures, 0 ignored)","cargo clippy -- -D warnings passes cleanly (no warnings)","cargo fmt --all --check passes (no formatting issues)","Amendment fr-15-03ed3b3d FIXED: record_task_run_start in fs.rs (lines 2827-2837) now calls fail_superseded_running_attempt() to auto-finalize the old running entry when a new runless retry with different started_at is appended. The fail_superseded_running_attempt function (lines 2662-2683) sets outcome=Failed, outcome_detail='superseded by retry started at {rfc3339}', finished_at=new retry's started_at. update_task_run with run_id=None uses is_superseded_legacy_start to filter out auto-failed entries, so the new retry remains the sole open match and can be finalized without ambiguity.","Amendment fr-15-03ed3b3d regression test: runless_retry_with_new_started_at_auto_fails_prior_attempt_and_stays_completable (service.rs) verifies: first attempt is auto-failed with 'superseded by retry' detail, second attempt is Running, then record_bead_completion succeeds, final snapshot has status=Ready with completed_beads=1 and failed_beads=0.","Amendment fr-15-ad53be55 FIXED: Lock files now live under milestones/.locks/<id>/ via milestone_lock_root (fs.rs:2098-2103, constant MILESTONE_LOCKS_DIR='.locks' at line 2089), separate from milestone data under milestones/<id>/. AdvisoryFileLock::acquire creates only the .locks/<id>/ directory, never the milestone data directory. milestone_exists (lines 2139-2151) only examines the data directory, so lock creation for a nonexistent milestone cannot poison that ID.","Amendment fr-15-ad53be55 regression test: update_task_run_missing_milestone_does_not_block_future_create (service.rs:1868-1911) calls update_task_run against a nonexistent milestone (fails), then successfully creates that milestone, proving no stale directory is left behind.","Amendment fr-15-ad53be55 regression test: persist_plan_missing_milestone_does_not_block_future_create also verifies the same property for persist_plan.","Amendment fr-15-967d37de FIXED: read_task_runs_from_path (fs.rs:2486-2521) now validates each deserialized entry's milestone_id against the expected milestone_id from the file path. Mismatches return AppError::CorruptRecord with line number and both IDs in the error message. find_runs_for_bead calls read_task_runs which delegates to read_task_runs_from_path, so the validation covers all downstream paths.","Amendment fr-15-967d37de regression test: misfiled_task_run_rows_are_rejected_by_queries_and_reconciliation (service.rs:1329-1379) seeds a task-run row with milestone_id='other-milestone' into the correct milestone's task-runs.ndjson, then asserts find_runs_for_bead fails with 'does not match milestone path' error.","model.rs: TaskRunEntry has all required fields — milestone_id (String, required), bead_id, project_id, run_id, plan_hash, outcome, outcome_detail, started_at, finished_at — with serde(default, skip_serializing_if) only on legitimately optional fields (run_id, plan_hash, outcome_detail, finished_at)","service.rs: reconcile_snapshot_from_lineage (lines 163-226) rebuilds counters from latest_task_runs_per_bead, preserves Paused status, transitions Active→Ready when no active beads remain, validates terminal invariants","service.rs: All mutation paths (update_status, persist_plan, record_bead_start, update_task_run) run under with_milestone_write_lock for serialized access","All original acceptance criteria remain satisfied: milestone state answers 'what happened to bead X?', controller can update linkage after each run outcome, no backward-compatibility with old schemas is needed"],"findings_or_gaps":["The outstanding risk — milestone mutations span separate lineage, snapshot, and journal files without a cross-file transaction — remains. All paths are serialized by the milestone mutation lock (per-milestone granularity) and replay-safe, making this an acceptable trade-off for file-based storage.","AppError::RunStartFailed is still used (service.rs ~line 555) for rejecting non-terminal outcomes in update_task_run, which is semantically a finalization rejection. A more specific error variant would be cleaner but this is cosmetic, not a correctness issue — carried forward from prior reviews.","The active_bead_ids() function in model.rs still contains its own internal latest_task_runs_per_bead() call while reconcile_snapshot_from_lineage computes latest runs separately. External callers of active_bead_ids would redundantly recompute, but this is minor and not a correctness concern.","Legacy runless attempts that persist after upgrades (run_id=None with no matching completion) remain visible in audit history as auto-failed entries with 'superseded by retry' detail, which is intentional and preserves the audit trail."],"follow_up_or_amendments":[],"outcome":"approved"},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"c85ba57c-63f9-484c-941c-584b717e816d"}
